news.title: Ludhiana: Vigilance starts inquiry into illegal structures in zone D
news.para: The chief vigilance officer of local bodies department has started an inquiry into a complaint filed against illegal constructions falling under the zone D of municipal corporation (MC).

news.title: How the old houses of Kolkata are learning to stand on their own feet
news.para: Architects say these old houses reflect Kolkata’s distinctive architectural legacy and reimagining them in the contemporary context is the need of the hour.

news.title: Over 700 solar street lights to illuminate 'dark lanes' of 32 Uttar Pradesh villages
news.para: A decision in this regard was taken on Friday in a meeting chaired by divisional commissioner Saharanpur Dr Lokesh M and attended by officials working on the project.

news.title: Jaipur development body to replace existing streetlights to 'smart intelligent lights'
news.para: The authority will also set up a Centralized Control &Monitoring System (CCMS) from where the streetlights can be managed.

news.title: Ashok Nagar nala shrinks as builders dump debris on the sly in Hyderabad
news.para: The dumping of debris has increased and being done more brazenly since the end of monsoon, residents said, adding that complaints to authorities has not yielded any results.

news.title: Plotted and sold: Land sharks bite into Kamuni Cheruvu in Hyderabad
news.para: GHMC officials said at least once acre of lake land had been encroached and a complaint filed to stop encroachments. GHMC (lakes division) assistant executive engineer A Lakshminarayana said they filed a complaint with Kukatpally police on November 7.

news.title: Migsun acquires 26 acres of land for Rs 220 crore in Lucknow
news.para: The company will develop 5 million sq ft on the acquired land with an investment of Rs 2,000 crore. Migsun group has completed more than 40 projects totalling about 20 million sq ft in various regions of Delhi-NCR during its three decades of operations.

news.title: Chennai development body single window sees rush for building approvals
news.para: ​"In June there were around 45 applications, and this shot up to 82 in October. Permissions for high rise buildings also rose. We gave 23 permissions in the last 5 months. It used to be just one a month," an official said.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP wants a pause on lease deeds of Raheja Developers & Brisk Infrastructure
news.para: District town planner Amit Madholia wrote to deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav that Raheja Developers and Brisk Infrastructure had failed to deposit the audit amounts despite repeated reminders.

news.title: China regulators urge more financing support for property firms: Sources
news.para: Several developers have defaulted on their offshore debt obligations over the past year, fuelling a property downturn which has weighed on the world's second-largest economy.

news.title: Structural audit of high-rises in Noida approved
news.para: The meeting was chaired by Uttar Pradesh Infrastructure and Industrial Development Commissioner and Noida Authority chairman Arvind Kumar with Noida Authority chief executive officer Ritu Maheshwari in presence.

news.title: Meghalaya CM awards land patta to over 100 tribal households in Reserve Gittim
news.para: The CEM is all set to award more than 100 land Pattas to tribal beneficiaries who are the rightful owners in recognition of their long-standing demand for rights over the land.

news.title: Keystone Realtors raises over Rs 190 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: Abu Dhabi Investment Authority, Morgan Stanley and Saint Capital accounted for nearly 35 per cent of the anchor investor portion.

news.title: Seven unsafe buildings in Chandrapur razed, eight others given final notices
news.para: CMC officials said they identified 15 such buildings and served notices to the occupants to vacate them. These included six buildings in Zone-I, eight in Zone-II and a solitary building in Zone-III.

news.title: Telangana: Granite businessmen cry foul over ED raids, say it's 'terrorising'
news.para: Reacting strongly to the searches, the Telangana Granite Industry Owners' Association said the Centre was terrorising the ailing granite industry.
